      "raw_text": "Senator A. J. Splawn Of North\nYakima, who represents the Fifteenth\ndistrict in the state legislature, has\nbeen in Spokane for the past two\ndays in the interest Of the state\nfair to be held at Yakima September\n2S to October 4. He met the cham\nDer of commerce and urged them to\ninterest Themselves in Yakima's fair.\n\n\nThe senator has q world Of sta\ntistics at his fingers end relative to\nthe Yakima valley which he char\nacterizes as one of the garden spots\nOf earth. Said the senator: ~\n\n\n\"Our fruit yield this year will net\nour people $1.000.Ooo several hun\nbred thousand over any previous\nyear. The alfalfa crop is worth a\nmillion and a half more. We grow\nhops worth 100000 and potatoes\nvalued at 100000."
